ffect of excess thyroid hormone?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Increased protein catabolism","Decreased cardiac contractility","Reduced sensitivity to adrenaline","Decreased basal metabolic rate","Reduced heat production"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThyroid hormones have widespread metabolic effects throughout the body. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased protein catabolism\u003C/strong\u003E is a characteristic finding in hyperthyroidism, leading to muscle wasting and contributing to weight loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased cardiac contractility\u003C/strong\u003E - Thyroid hormones increase cardiac contractility and heart rate\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced sensitivity to adrenaline\u003C/strong\u003E - Thyroid hormones upregulate beta-adrenergic receptors, increasing sensitivity to catecholamines\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased basal metabolic rate\u003C/strong\u003E - Thyroid hormones increase metabolic rate\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced heat production\u003C/strong\u003E - Thyroid hormones increase thermogenesis\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe metabolic effects of thyroid hormones explain many clinical features of hyperthyroidism including weight loss despite normal appetite, tremor, heat intolerance, and tachycardia.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Thyroid hormones increase protein catabolism leading to muscle wasting and weight loss","Thyroid hormones increase basal metabolic rate and heat production","Thyroid hormones enhance beta-adrenergic receptor sensitivity causing sympathetic symptoms"],"references":["Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine Syst